"HELP 
 
 Pension Benefit 
 Pension received from a former employer is fully exempt from tax. However, if youre still working for your previous employer or any of its associate company, then it is not exempt and must be reported under Salary Income. 
 
 Further, in case youre receiving pension from multiple employers then enter the higher pension amount as pension income and report the remaining pension income under Salary Income."

"HELP 
 
 WITHHOLDING TAXES ON PAYMENTS: 
 The Government has required certain persons to withhold taxes on payments against various transactions including sale of goods, rendering of services, and execution of contracts. 
 Such withholding taxes are considered as minimum tax while determining the final tax liability of the business on net-income basis"

"HELP 
 
 Tax Concessions for Exporters of IT Enabled Services and Startups: 
 Export of IT Services are allowed 100% tax credit i.e. no tax on income from IT related export services if exporter of IT services (i.e. the taxpayer) has brought at least eighty percent of export proceeds into Pakistan through normal banking channel. 
 
 Similarly, Profits and gains of startups that are certified by the Pakistan Software Export Board (PSEB) are also eligible for claiming 100% tax credit from income tax in the year of certification by PSEB and the following two years"
